00:30:20.900 --> 00:30:24.710
recognizing that ultimately,
at the of the day,

00:30:24.710 --> 00:30:27.950
your goal presumably is to get
productive work out of these--

00:30:27.950 --> 00:30:29.480
out of your employees.

00:30:29.480 --> 00:30:32.930
And there's just a lot of
evidence that providing people

00:30:32.930 --> 00:30:34.430
with the flexibility
that they need,

00:30:34.430 --> 00:30:36.554
and the time off they need
to recover, to make sure

00:30:36.554 --> 00:30:38.780
that their kid
recovers from the flu,

00:30:38.780 --> 00:30:41.370
all can be
productivity enhancing.

00:30:41.370 --> 00:30:44.960
And all can do a lot
to reduce job turnover

00:30:44.960 --> 00:30:47.210
and increase retention.

00:30:47.210 --> 00:30:50.720
A number of years ago a
