00:30:50.720 --> 00:30:52.430
looked at all the
good studies we

00:30:52.430 --> 00:30:55.790
could find on the
cost of job turnover,

00:30:55.790 --> 00:30:58.390
and what that looks like
across the wage spectrum.

00:30:58.390 --> 00:31:00.200
Because you hear
like, oh yeah well,

00:31:00.200 --> 00:31:01.760
job turnover can
be very expensive

00:31:01.760 --> 00:31:04.640
if you have a very
important employee that you

00:31:04.640 --> 00:31:06.500
have to replace
but for those line

00:31:06.500 --> 00:31:07.970
workers, or those
retail workers,

00:31:07.970 --> 00:31:10.178
it's nothing, it doesn't
matter like cost of turnover

00:31:10.178 --> 00:31:11.630
is really low or something.

00:31:11.630 --> 00:31:13.640
You sort of here that
in the common discourse.

00:31:13.640 --> 00:31:15.931
So at any rate, we looked at
every study we could find,

00:31:15.931 --> 00:31:18.314
and this was maybe almost
like eight years ago

00:31:18.314 --> 00:31:20.480
that I did this so I'm sure
there's new studies that

00:31:20.480 --> 00:31:23.730
have come out but, of all
the studies we could find,

00:31:23.730 --> 00:31:25.850
we found that if you
look across people--

00:31:25.850 --> 00:31:28.700
and again this was a while ago--
but people were paid from like

00:31:28.700 --> 00:31:31.949
$20-$30,000 a year all the way
up to about $75,000 a year,

00:31:31.949 --> 00:31:34.490
which in today's dollars would
probably be closer to about 80

00:31:34.490 --> 00:31:36.320
or 90.

00:31:36.320 --> 00:31:38.630
The cost of
replacing an employee

00:31:38.630 --> 00:31:42.950
was about a fifth of that
employee's annual salary.

00:31:42.950 --> 00:31:46.970
So as a manager, really
thinking about the fact that,

00:31:46.970 --> 00:31:50.210
hey this person just wants
a little bit of flexibility,

00:31:50.210 --> 00:31:53.030
and maybe they won't be
more productive this week,

00:31:53.030 --> 00:31:54.940
but if the difference
between keeping

00:31:54.940 --> 00:31:58.330
that employee for another
year or six months and not.

00:31:58.330 --> 00:32:01.940
That actually has enormous
savings for the corporation.

00:32:01.940 --> 00:32:06.250
And you know, too often,
that calculus of those costs

00:32:06.250 --> 00:32:08.860
don't seem to be sort
of worked in to some

00:32:08.860 --> 00:32:13.087
of these line manager
thinking, at least

00:32:13.087 --> 00:32:14.170
according to the evidence.

00:32:14.170 --> 00:32:18.010
So yeah, so that's some
advice I have for you

